mary_text\",\"text\":\"**Planning test naming conventions**\\n\\nI'm considering how the user wants durable naming and verifying compilation but there are active instructions against running tests now. It seems like using binary names instead of canonical ones is the right route. For the test class, it looks like `PatchFixesHiderInnerUtilTest` aligns with existing rules. Current tests seem to violate the LombokTest package-private settings, but I should note build config already has necessary modifications. It's important to maintain clarity moving forward!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class dependencies**\\n\\nI need to avoid mentioning the editing of current configurations. I’m considering whether the class name could cause issues with native reflection, especially since `PatchFixesShadowLoaded` relies on other service files. The simple method starts with `Version`, possibly from `lombok.core.Version`, which seems relevant. The `shadowLoadClass` initializes successfully without errors. The agent's native configuration covers this. It looks like I can find methods and invoke through the target, so I should keep my answer concise yet detailed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "## Findings\n\n`PatchFixesHider.Util` is a JVM-public bridge for Lombok’s Eclipse bytecode patches. Its enclosing class is package-private, but the compiled binary class `lombok.launch.PatchFixesHider$Util` is public; follow-up tests can reference that binary name from an external test package.\n\nNormal Lombok annotation processing (`@Value`, `@Builder`, etc.) does **not** reach this class. The existing `testAnnotationProcessor` setup remains useful for Lombok coverage generally, but is unrelated to these five calls.\n\nThe Eclipse-agent route (`EclipsePatcher` → transformed Eclipse/ECJ classes) would require runtime instrumentation and bytecode transformation, so it must not be used.\n\n## Safe collaborator fixture\n\nUse Lombok’s public `lombok.eclipse.agent.PatchFixesShadowLoaded`:\n\n- It is the normal shadow-loaded implementation used by `PatchFixesHider.LombokDeps`.\n- Its unique static method `addLombokNotesToEclipseAboutDialog(String, String)` is safe to invoke.\n- With `\"aboutText\"`, it returns the original text plus Lombok installation text; assert stable content such as `\" is installed. https://projectlombok.org/\"`, not a version string.\n\n## Coverage plan\n\nCreate exactly one dedicated external test file:\n\n`src/test/java/org_projectlombok/lombok/PatchFixesHiderInnerUtilTest.java`\n\nwith a public top-level class. The `InnerUtil` name follows the required `$Util` naming conversion.\n\nExercise the bridge directly through its public binary API:\n\n| Call site | Test action |\n|---|---|\n| `Class.forName(String, boolean, ClassLoader)` | Call `PatchFixesHider$Util.shadowLoadClass(\"lombok.eclipse.agent.PatchFixesShadowLoaded\")`; assert it returns `PatchFixesShadowLoaded.class`. |\n| `Class.getDeclaredMethod(...)` | Call `findMethod(PatchFixesShadowLoaded.class, \"addLombokNotesToEclipseAboutDialog\", String.class, String.class)`. |\n| `Class.getDeclaredMethods()` via named parameter types | Call the `findMethod(Class, String, String...)` overload using two `\"java.lang.String\"` parameter names; assert it identifies the same method. |\n| `Class.getDeclaredMethods()` via any args | Call `findMethodAnyArgs(PatchFixesShadowLoaded.class, \"addLombokNotesToEclipseAboutDialog\")`; the method name is unique on this fixture. |\n| `Method.invoke(...)` | Pass a discovered `Method` to `invokeMethod(method, \"Original\", \"aboutText\")`; assert the returned value preserves `\"Original\"` and contains the stable installed-text suffix. |\n\nUsing `Method` as the value returned by and passed back to Lombok’s public bridge is natural API use, not direct test reflection.\n\n## Do not pursue\n\n- Annotation-processor-only tests: they do not load `PatchFixesHider.Util`.\n- `Agent`, `AgentLauncher`, or `EclipsePatcher` execution: this requires `Instrumentation`, class transformation, and Eclipse/ECJ integration.\n- Negative lookup paths: `shadowLoadClass` and the lookup helpers rethrow missing-class/missing-method failures and provide no supported behavior worth asserting.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0937a963dedf3425016a4b83f868f08191bffc558a5928eae0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-codex-responses", "provider": "openai-codex", "model": "gpt-5.6-terra", "usage": {"input": 1002, "output": 2741, "cacheRead": 55296, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59039, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1783333836176, "responseId": "resp_0937a963dedf3425016a4b83ccdb688191a5670fadea9514df"}, "toolResults": []}
